# Frontend conventions

- Product brand in UI: **La Queta** (see `STYLE_GUIDE.md` §5).
- Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS only — no React/Vue/Tailwind/Bootstrap/HTMX.
- Tokens and visual rules live in `STYLE_GUIDE.md` §4–5 (gold-washed surface, Senyera red CTAs, gold progress/highlights, Fraunces display / Figtree UI). No flag strip.
- **Multi-page:** one URL per job (`/`, `/levels`, `/levels/<id>`, `/levels/<id>/daily`, `/lessons/<id>`, `/decks/<slug>`, `/study`, `/browse`). Extend `templates/base.html`. Do not revive a hidden-section mega-page.
- Gate: **Create account** (name + email + password) / **Sign in** (email + password). No OAuth. Taglines show `user.handle`.
- Page JS under `static/js/` (`api.js` shared). Mutations still hit `/api/…`.
- Component gallery: `/style-guide`. New UI patterns must be added there in the same change.
- Level hub: A1 clickable; A2/B1 disabled tiles (“coming soon”). Daily vocab CTA on level page. Can-do checklist on Learn tab.
- Study: first-load tip dialog (Don’t show again); tap / Enter / Next = flip then next (seen++); Back = previous; Retire confirm dialog (`localStorage`). Card `hint` only when pedagogical. Empty/finished session → redirect to exit URL (deck or level vocab). Daily session via `/levels/<id>/daily`.
- Lesson: Learn | Practice tabs (`?tab=`). Practice kinds: MC, cloze, type-in, **listen_choice / listen_type / speak** (browser TTS via `speech.js`; speak is self-check, optional mic). Accents required on typed answers.
- Deck page: retired progress bar; when fully retired, **Unretire deck** (resets seen → 0) instead of Study.
- Browse: retired rows muted + badge; Retire button on active cards.
- Vocab flashcards/browse show prototype meta on the Catalan side: pronunciation, grammar pills (`pos` / gender / plural), verb forms, tags. Keep study flip meta Catalan-only.
- Mobile-first; keep motion minimal and intentional.
- Prefer extending `static/app.css` / `static/js/*` over new frameworks.
- Author CSS that sets `display` must not fight `[hidden]` — keep `[hidden] { display: none !important; }`.
